<div class="lang-en">
<section id="wood">
  <h2>Wood Element (<span class="chinese-char">木</span>) &mdash; Years Ending in 4 or 5</h2>
  <p><strong>Direction:</strong> East &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Season:</strong> Spring &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Colour:</strong> Green &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Organ:</strong> Liver</p>
  <p>Wood represents growth, expansion, and upward movement &mdash; think of a bamboo shoot pushing through stone. People born in Wood years tend to be <strong>creative, generous, and idealistic</strong>. They are natural planners who think in long time horizons and value community over individual gain.</p>
  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong> Vision, compassion, artistic talent, cooperative spirit. Wood people build institutions, nurture talent, and think systemically.</p>
  <p><strong>Challenges:</strong> Indecisiveness, overextension, difficulty saying no. Wood's desire to grow in all directions can lead to scattered energy. Under stress, Wood turns rigid rather than flexible &mdash; stubbornness masquerading as principle.</p>
  <p><strong>Example:</strong> A Wood Rat (1984) combines the Rat's resourcefulness with Wood's generosity, producing a person who is both shrewd and community-minded &mdash; an excellent networker with genuine warmth.</p>
</section>
</div>
<div class="lang-tc">
<section id="wood">
  <h2>木元素（<span class="chinese-char">木</span>）——尾數4或5的年份</h2>
  <p><strong>方位：</strong>東 &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>季節：</strong>春 &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>顏色：</strong>綠色 &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>臟腑：</strong>肝</p>
  <p>木代表生長、擴展和向上的力量——如同竹筍破石而出。木年出生的人往往<strong>富有創造力、慷慨大方且理想主義</strong>。他們是天生的規劃者，著眼長遠，重視群體利益勝於個人得失。</p>
  <p><strong>優勢：</strong>遠見、同理心、藝術天賦、合作精神。木命人善於建立制度、培育人才、系統性思考。</p>
  <p><strong>挑戰：</strong>優柔寡斷、過度擴張、難以拒絕。木的向各方生長的特性可能導致精力分散。壓力之下，木會變得僵硬而非靈活——以原則之名行固執之實。</p>
  <p><strong>舉例：</strong>木鼠（1984年）將鼠的機智與木的慷慨結合，形成一個既精明又重視群體的人——一位真誠熱情的出色社交者。</p>
</section>
</div>
